Martins Ifijeh The Lagos State Government has discharged 13 additional COVID-19 patients from its isolation centres, bringing to 662 the number of persons successfully treated in the state. Announcing this Thursday, the Incident Commander on COVID-19 in Lagos State, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, said nine of the patients were males, while four were females, adding that they were all Nigerians. He said: “Five were discharged from the Lagos University Teaching Hospital (LUTH), four from Eti-Osa (LandMark) Isolation Centre, three from Lekki Isolation Centre, while one was from the Onikan Isolation Centre. “With this, the number of COVID-19 confirmed cases that have been successfully managed and discharged in Lagos has risen to 662,” he added